#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/communications/asterisk_installation.md:14
#, no-wrap
msgid "    The last version of Rocky Linux that this procedure was tested on was version 8.5. Because the bulk of this procedure relies on source builds directly from Asterisk and a simple set of Development Tools from Rocky Linux, it should work on all versions. If you run into a problem, please let us know!\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title #
#: ../src/docs/guides/communications/asterisk_installation.md:15
#, no-wrap
msgid "Installing Asterisk on Rocky Linux"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/communications/asterisk_installation.md:18
#, no-wrap
msgid "**What is Asterisk?**\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/communications/asterisk_installation.md:20
#, no-wrap
msgid "Asterisk is an open source framework for building communications applications. Additionally, Asterisk turns an ordinary computer into a communications server, as well as powering IP PBX systems, VoIP gateways, conference servers and other custom solutions. It is used by small businesses, large businesses, call centers, carriers, and government agencies worldwide.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/communications/asterisk_installation.md:22
#, no-wrap
msgid "Asterisk is free and open source and is sponsored by [Sangoma](https://www.sangoma.com/). Sangoma also offers commercial products that use Asterisk under the hood, and depending on your experience and budget, using these products may be more beneficial than rolling your own. Only you and your organization know that answer.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/communications/asterisk_installation.md:24
#, no-wrap
msgid "It should be noted that this guide requires the administrator to do a fair amount of research on their own. Installing a communications server is not a difficult process, but running one can be quite complicated. While this guide will get your server up and running, it will not be fully ready for you to use in production.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/communications/asterisk_installation.md:28
#, no-wrap
msgid "At minimum, you will need the following skills and tools to complete this guide:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: ../src/docs/guides/communications/asterisk_installation.md:36
#, no-wrap
msgid "A machine running Rocky Linux\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: ../src/docs/guides/communications/asterisk_installation.md:36
#, no-wrap
msgid "A comfort level with modifying configuration files and issuing commands from the command-line\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: ../src/docs/guides/communications/asterisk_installation.md:36
#, no-wrap
msgid "Knowledge of how to use a command line editor (We are using `vi` here, but feel free to substitute in your favorite editor.)\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: ../src/docs/guides/communications/asterisk_installation.md:36
#, no-wrap
msgid "The ability to login as root or run root commands with _sudo_. All commands here assume a user that has _sudo_ rights, however the configuration and build processes are run with `sudo -s`.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: ../src/docs/guides/communications/asterisk_installation.md:36
#, no-wrap
msgid "To grab the latest build of Asterisk, you will need to either use `curl` or `wget`. This guide uses `wget`, but feel free to substitute in the appropriate `curl` string if you want to use that.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: ../src/docs/guides/communications/asterisk_installation.md:37
#, no-wrap
msgid "Update Rocky Linux and Install `wget`"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block
#: ../src/docs/guides/communications/asterisk_installation.md:39
#, no-wrap
msgid "sudo dnf -y update\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/communications/asterisk_installation.md:44
#, no-wrap
msgid "This will get your server up-to-date with all packages that have been released or updated since the last update or install. Then run:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block
#: ../src/docs/guides/communications/asterisk_installation.md:45
#, no-wrap
msgid "sudo dnf install wget\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: ../src/docs/guides/communications/asterisk_installation.md:49
#, no-wrap
msgid "Set Hostname"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/communications/asterisk_installation.md:52
#, no-wrap
msgid "Set your host name to the domain you'll be using for Asterisk.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block
#: ../src/docs/guides/communications/asterisk_installation.md:53
#, no-wrap
msgid "sudo hostnamectl set-hostname asterisk.example.com\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: ../src/docs/guides/communications/asterisk_installation.md:57
#, no-wrap
msgid "Add Needed Repositories"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/communications/asterisk_installation.md:60
#, no-wrap
msgid "First, install the EPEL (Extra Packages for Enterprise Linux):\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block
#: ../src/docs/guides/communications/asterisk_installation.md:61
#, no-wrap
msgid "sudo dnf -y install epel-release\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/communications/asterisk_installation.md:66
#, no-wrap
msgid "Next, enable Rocky Linux' PowerTools:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block
#: ../src/docs/guides/communications/asterisk_installation.md:67
#, no-wrap
msgid "sudo dnf config-manager --set-enabled powertools\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: ../src/docs/guides/communications/asterisk_installation.md:71
#, no-wrap
msgid "Install Development Tools"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block
#: ../src/docs/guides/communications/asterisk_installation.md:73
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"sudo dnf group -y install \"Development Tools\"\n"
"sudo dnf -y install git wget  \n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: ../src/docs/guides/communications/asterisk_installation.md:78
#, no-wrap
msgid "Install Asterisk"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#: ../src/docs/guides/communications/asterisk_installation.md:80
#, no-wrap
msgid "Downloading and Configuring the Asterisk Build"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/communications/asterisk_installation.md:83
#, no-wrap
msgid "Before you download this script, make sure you have the latest version. To do so, navigate to [the Asterisk download link here](http://downloads.asterisk.org/pub/telephony/asterisk/) and look for the latest build of Asterisk. Then copy the link location. As of the writing of this document, the following was the latest build:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block
#: ../src/docs/guides/communications/asterisk_installation.md:84
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"wget http://downloads.asterisk.org/pub/telephony/asterisk/asterisk-20-current.tar.gz \n"
"tar xvfz asterisk-20-current.tar.gz\n"
"cd asterisk-20.0.0/\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/communications/asterisk_installation.md:91
#, no-wrap
msgid "Before running the `install_prereq` below (and the remaining commands), you are going to need to be the superuser or root. It's much easier at this point to get into _sudo_ permanently for a while. We will exit back out of _sudo_ later in the process:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block
#: ../src/docs/guides/communications/asterisk_installation.md:92
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"sudo -s\n"
"contrib/scripts/install_prereq install\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/communications/asterisk_installation.md:98
#, no-wrap
msgid "You should see the following when the script completes:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block
#: ../src/docs/guides/communications/asterisk_installation.md:99
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"#############################################\n"
"## install completed successfully\n"
"#############################################\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/communications/asterisk_installation.md:106
#, no-wrap
msgid "Now that all of the required packages are installed, our next step is to configure and build Asterisk:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block
#: ../src/docs/guides/communications/asterisk_installation.md:107
#, no-wrap
msgid "./configure --libdir=/usr/lib64 --with-jansson-bundled=yes\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/communications/asterisk_installation.md:112
#, no-wrap
msgid "Assuming that the configuration runs without issue, you should get a large ASCII  Asterisk emblem, followed by the following on Rocky Linux:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block
#: ../src/docs/guides/communications/asterisk_installation.md:113
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"configure: Package configured for:\n"
"configure: OS type  : linux-gnu\n"
"configure: Host CPU : x86_64\n"
"configure: build-cpu:vendor:os: x86_64 : pc : linux-gnu :\n"
"configure: host-cpu:vendor:os: x86_64 : pc : linux-gnu :\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#: ../src/docs/guides/communications/asterisk_installation.md:121
#, no-wrap
msgid "Set Asterisk menu options [For more options]"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/communications/asterisk_installation.md:124
#, no-wrap
msgid "This is one of the steps where the administrator is going to need to do his homework. There are a lot of menu options that you may or may not need. Running the following command:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block
#: ../src/docs/guides/communications/asterisk_installation.md:125
#, no-wrap
msgid "make menuselect\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/communications/asterisk_installation.md:130
#, no-wrap
msgid "will bring you to a menu select screen:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/communications/asterisk_installation.md:132
#, no-wrap
msgid "![menuselect screen](../images/asterisk_menuselect.png)\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/communications/asterisk_installation.md:134
#, no-wrap
msgid "Look through these options carefully and make selections based on your requirements. As stated earlier, this may take some additional homework.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#: ../src/docs/guides/communications/asterisk_installation.md:135
#, no-wrap
msgid "Build and Install Asterisk"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/communications/asterisk_installation.md:138
#, no-wrap
msgid "To build, we want to execute the following commands in succession:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block
#: ../src/docs/guides/communications/asterisk_installation.md:139
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"make\n"
"make install\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/communications/asterisk_installation.md:145
#, no-wrap
msgid "Installing the documentation isn't required, but unless you are a communications server expert, you'll want them installed:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block
#: ../src/docs/guides/communications/asterisk_installation.md:146
#, no-wrap
msgid "make progdocs\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/communications/asterisk_installation.md:151
#, no-wrap
msgid "Next install the basic PBX and make the config. The basic PBX is just that, very basic! You will probably need to make changes going forward to get your PBX to function as you want it to.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block
#: ../src/docs/guides/communications/asterisk_installation.md:152
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"make basic-pbx\n"
"make config\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: ../src/docs/guides/communications/asterisk_installation.md:157
#, no-wrap
msgid "Asterisk Configuration"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#: ../src/docs/guides/communications/asterisk_installation.md:159
#, no-wrap
msgid "Create User & Group"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/communications/asterisk_installation.md:162
#, no-wrap
msgid "You'll need a specific user just for asterisk. Might as well create it now.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block
#: ../src/docs/guides/communications/asterisk_installation.md:163
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"groupadd asterisk\n"
"useradd -r -d /var/lib/asterisk -g asterisk asterisk\n"
"chown -R asterisk.asterisk /etc/asterisk /var/{lib,log,spool}/asterisk /usr/lib64/asterisk\n"
"restorecon -vr {/etc/asterisk,/var/lib/asterisk,/var/log/asterisk,/var/spool/asterisk}\n"
